Feedback: When you asked about stereotypes, I think it's important to remember that stereotyping has been useful for our evolutionary history. Humans stereotype for survival reasons (safety, value). While stereotyping for purposefully mean reasons is obviously wrong, I think society is missing why humans have ever stereotyped in the first place. Prejudice is partly to blame, but sometimes stereotypes exist for a reason.
